task.summary: Default task

Hello LAMBDA! THANKS MR. INTELLIJ
Changed all of the input listeners to Lambda functions. Also spent most of this time switching to IntelliJ.
Test code for the startup menu.

Major refactor, with the main intent of following the Single Responsibility Design Principle. (Software engineering whaaaaaaat) - Moved all GUI initialization from main to the GUI class. - Simplified Main completely. - Added some working functions to GUI class for later use - Changed StartupMenu into a SplitPane (instead of... whatever it was) - Test code now features a custom ColorPicker!
Slowly moving towards more flexible, reliable code :>

This is the TRIFORCE* COMMIT!
Hacked together a release. Now, I'm not exactly sure what it looked like on the last commit, but I definitely see a hell of a lot of red in the file explorer, so this comment probably won't cover everything. (I'm just gonna read off the red.)
- Created the ScreenController, along with the abstract Screen class (and a few subclasses). See comments for details! - Implemented a basic version of the Overview and Startup Menu, as well as added placeholders for the other screens. - Mustered some implementation of the EntryCell interface. - Implemented a popup for adding Entries that showcases how hard it actually ISN'T. - Realized I spend too much time writing commit comments. - Red, green(ish)... very BADLY need to refactor. - *Tapped into my ability to do a lot, very quickly.
Here's to the future.
Added files to version control. No more red - now everything's green!

Triforce Commit, Part 3 - Closing the Trilogy 3 chances. 3 days. 1 future secured.
- Working random Project generator - EntryAreas generate branches! - Fixed BubbleEntry corner-clicking glitch (still needs work, but it's MUCH better now) - Maaad toString() methods (for that sweet debuggy goodness) - EntryCell is now an abstract class instead of an interface (which actually makes sense) - Significantly improved stress management*
Keep calm and unfuck this shit up!
*Necessary for the... significantly increased stress.

Triforce Commit, Part 3 - Closing the Trilogy 3 chances. 3 days. 1 future secured.
- Working random Project generator - EntryAreas generate branches! - Fixed BubbleEntry corner-clicking glitch (still needs work, but it's MUCH better now) - Maaad toString() methods (for that sweet debuggy goodness) - EntryCell is now an abstract class instead of an interface (which actually makes sense) - Significantly improved stress management*
Keep calm and unfuck this shit up!
*Necessary for the... significantly increased stress.

Refactoring & Breaking stuff
- Refactored EntryCell, BubbleEntry, and ListEntry creation (especially on startup) - Removed Labels from the EntryCell subclasses (only uses TextFields now) - Rounded out the Bubbles - Broke focused entries
Un-broke focusing!
- Fixed & refactored ListEntry creation. - Indents are broken.
- Indents fixed.
- Un-broke ListEntry display. - ListEntries now preserve their expanded status when switching between BubbleEntries. - Less "blinking" when switching between Bubbles.
- Expand/retract behavior localized to their individual EntryCell objects. - Refactored creation of new entries. - Separated the actual expansion/retraction from setting the focus
- Fixed shift-click - Added deselecting functionality with Ctrl+click
- Selecting ListEntries no longer retracts BubbleEntries
- Styled the TitleBar & ViewBar
- Added methods for Date processing (on new in-between Entries)
- Added method to swap Entries like a boss
- Fixed ListView visual
- Thin branches, and branches between bubbles.
- Refined branches. (Still need branches on startup!)
This is the latest version of the project before the hard drive failed.
